Package com.snapbundle.model.context

Collection of SnapBundle context modeling artifacts.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    IAccount
    Collection of foundational attributes that define a platform subscription.
    IDevice
    Identifies a specific type of computation device and a means of uniquely identifying a specific device.
    IFile
    Represents any type of multimedia file that is explicitly associated with a single IReferentialObject.
    IMetadata
    Specific instance of a type-safe key-value pair linked to a singular referential object within the account's data set.
    IObject
    Foundational artifact within the SnapBundle platform used to represent nouns, e.g.
    IObjectAddress
    Captures a political address for a specific IObject.
    IObjectInteraction
    Captures an explicit interaction between two existing IObject instances that already exist in the system.
    IObjectInteractionSession
    Simple construct used to establish a logical albeit arbitrarily defined peer relationship between a collection of IObjectInteraction instances.
    IRelationship
    Captures binary or true-false conditions between objects.
    ITag
    Defines a word or phrase useful for searching across related objects.
    ITagAssignment
    Captures a ITag assignment with a specific IReferentialObject within a specific account context.
    ITimelineEntry
    Defines a historically significant event identified by name and a specific timestamp, optionally clarified by an optional description.
    IUser
    System user with login and query privileges.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    MetadataDataType
    Supported type-safe data types supported by IMetadata.
    RoleType
    Minimalist set of security roles.

Package com.snapbundle.model.context Description

Collection of SnapBundle context modeling artifacts. The interfaces and enumerations within this package form the foundation for the major contextual object model components.
